Username Display -- Version 2.2

Someone wanted a plugin to show the current username so they didn't get
mixed up with their numerous accounts.


Features
========

* Positionable
* Three different formats for displaying
* Able to be disabled


Description
===========

Just shows the username in a box either above or below the list of folders
and/or as the "Message Of The Day".


Future Work
===========

* Ideas?


Change Log
==========

  * v2.3 29/08/03 Paul Lesneiwski <pdontthink@angrynerds.com>
      Added the ability for the username and the regular MOTD
      to coexist (or for the MOTD to be overwritten - this is
      configurable).
      Added new configuration file.

  * v2.2 23/06/03 Paul Lesneiwski <pdontthink@angrynerds.com>
      Added the ability for administrators to indicate that "@domain.com"
      should be added to username display

  * v2.1 14/06/03 Paul Lesneiwski <pdontthink@angrynerds.com>
      Option to put username into a welcome message displayed where
      the Message Of The Day appears.
      Shrunk the display of the username above/below the folder 
      list with usage of proportional font.  Ahhh.

  * v2.0 26/03/03 Paul Lesneiwski <pdontthink@angrynerds.com>
      Updated for compatibility with SquirrelMail v1.4
      Internationalized all output
      New setup.php format for better overall SquirralMail performance

  * v1.1 13/02/03 Paul Lesneiwski <pdontthink@angrynerds.com>
      Made compatible with register_globals = Off
      Made compatible with Plugin Updates plugin 
   
  * v1.0 - Initial version



Questions/comments/flames/etc can be sent to the SquirrelMail Plugins list.

